commit 546df51cb114ba7387c480a766a7d1c05c5a2f7a
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 17:03:20 2026 -0400

    feat(forms)(form-engine): delete the three old schemas + oracle once the harness is green
    
    The equivalence harnesses (contact/volunteer/registration) and the kept
    registration oracle (`registration-schema.oracle.ts`) were transient migration
    scaffolding: they proved engine-vs-oracle behaviour parity over a full failure
    matrix while the structural Form engine was built (Branch 6.3-6.5). With every
    form migration green, ADR 0007's removal condition is met ("the oracle is removed
    once registration is fully migrated"), so this sub-commit subtracts them.
    
    migrate-callers-then-delete-legacy-apis: registration-form.tsx no longer borrows
    the oracle's precise registrant `.Type` for conform's field-accessor metadata.
    The form now owns its field-name contract as a local `RegistrantInput` Schema
    (the encoded/form-input shape it renders `name=`s for) and casts the engine
    StandardSchema to it at the seam. Runtime validation still flows entirely from
    the engine (`definitionToSchema(defaultRegistrationForm)`); derive-dont-sync.
    
    The registration render-parity tests OUTLIVE the oracle (they never depended on
    it): they assert the live <RegistrationForm> emits submit-names matching the
    definition graph and that makeDefaultRegistrant seeds every rendered field — the
    `cameraOperator`/`photographer`-class regression guard. Moved to
    `forms/registration-form.test.tsx`. Engine decode behaviour is covered standalone
    by decode.test.ts / definition.test.ts / render.test.tsx.
    
    Stale oracle-path doc references in decode.ts and defaults.ts updated to past
    tense. -1533 net lines; the deletion test passes.

